Description: Plaster outer jar-sealing bearing four impressions of a seal engraved with the plumed and disked cartouche of King Nekau II
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (D), "floor" of chamber 22
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 22 is pencilled on the object.
